I realize it's my fault, I fell in love with Iveta and that's why I take any responsibility.
The worst female vices: What about you?
If you ask men to name some typical female vices, they invariably shake some out of their sleeves.
Dear women, do you recognize yourself in the following lines, in which we review a few bad habits that make the blood flow in the veins of men?
Shopping addiction
Does her husband accuse her of being addicted to shopping?
Do you need to buy at least one Hader a week?
Do you like to go shopping and would you like a little more when it comes to promotions?
Then in your case it is probably really about a weakness.
Some women are at least aware of this and try to keep their desire to shop halfway under control.
But hand on heart, what woman can stand to stroll through a clothing store in search of a well-fitting outerwear and not try out all of them (in all possible color combinations) in the cabin?
Even though shopping is a hobby for most women, for men it is often pure hell.
Think about how many times you have told your husband - you better stay outside...
Constant dissatisfaction
"Am I not too fat?"
"I would have to lose at least five kilos - should I start jogging or doing gymnastics?"
"Do you like me at all?"
Does this sound familiar to you?
Yes?
Then you are probably one of those women who are obsessed with how they look.
This does not mean that you should let yourself go, but many men are allergic to it when their wife constantly complains about her appearance.
The stronger sex agrees - with increasing frequency of complaints, women are more and more incompatible.
Order and cleanliness first
It is a battle against windmills.
Clean windows, wipe tiles and dust, scrub the tub - at least twice a week.
Do you scold your partner because he tramples on the clean tiles with dirty shoes again, scold the children because the sink that has just been scrubbed is dirty again and because the glass door on the living room cabinet has fingerprints again, when polishing is so much trouble?
If you suffer from this kind of "deviance", then you should know that one should not exaggerate anything and that order and cleanliness do not come first in family life.
This excessive purity frenzy can ultimately damage mutual relationships and, above all, peace in the family.
Tease
"Dirty gym pants go in the laundry basket."
"Do you really want to put those old socks back on tomorrow?"
"You don't just throw a wet towel on the floor."
If your partner is exposed to such a tirade, you should not be surprised that it makes him angry.
Of course, that's not bad, they just want everything to be in order.
If the men knew this, then the women might not need to complain so much.
Gossip
Some women like to gossip and gossip, whispering or even slandering behind their backs or making alliances.
Women are focused on relationships, so they like to rush through such topics as - who, where, with whom, how and why.
Probably every one of us women has a bit of harmless gossip in store.
Hand on heart - this is probably characteristic of all women.
But this is not to be confused with gossipers of the crudest caliber, to whom nothing and no one is sacred, who probably despise everyone around them and who pose a considerable danger, especially for women's collectives.
