After the discovery of the "Zwickau cell", Turkish media doubt the German rule of law.
One newspaper even speaks of a "bloody ideology" that is now reviving.
The murders of eight Turkish-born and one Greek small business owner between 2000 and 2006 had a right-wing extremist background.
This news is being reacted to with fear and concern in Turkey and within the German-Turkish population in Germany.
