In a second attempt, the clever crows then had to solve a trickier problem.
In a vertical cylinder, the researchers had placed a small bucket with a moth larva.
With the beak, the birds could not reach their prey.
However, the researchers had laid pieces of wire in front of them.
From this, all four animals formed a hook, with the help of which they then fished the bucket by the handle out of the tube.
Three of the four rooks even succeeded in doing so right away.
