In fact, since 2002 this has been the subject of constant monitoring and political offensives, which have borne fruit most frequently.
The French are no longer sick more often than people elsewhere in Europe.
However, let us first dwell on the national figures.
According to the national health insurance fund CNAM, more than 237 million euros in daily severance payments were paid out in 2006.
According to the Economic Research and Documentation Institute of Health Care, daily severance payments accounted for 11.3 billion euros in 2008, 5% of health expenditure.
This amount included 46% for maternity leave and accidents at work and 54% for sick leave, i.e. 6.2 billion euros.
And therefore 2.5% health expenditure.
