Among the systematically controlled sick leave cases lasting more than 45 days, 11% of 1.2 million cases were "non-conformist or unjustified", i.e. 132,000.
In total, this makes 169,000 "unjustified" cases for several million workers who have claimed sick leave.
A figure that represents only a weak extent compared to, for example, that of undeclared work.
According to UMP MP Dominique Tian, author of a factual report on this issue published in July, this represents between €9 billion and €15 billion in lost tax profits per year, i.e. more than the total cost of daily pay, and thus much more than the defrauding of the latter.
