Portugal very confident
Paulo Bento's Portuguese team is looking forward with great optimism to the second leg against Bosnia (22:00) this Tuesday in Lisbon.
In the first leg, both teams had lacked objectivity.
"At the end of these 90 minutes we will be a happy team and above all a happy country."
Paulo Bento already sees himself in Poland and Ukraine.
For him, there is not the slightest hint of doubt that "La Selecçao", his national team, for which he has been responsible since September 2010, will qualify for the 2012 European Championship.
For Portugal, in fact, this means only 90 minutes of bliss.
